thread.title: Homemade Highlights: The Battle for Big Air Snowboarding Gold

author: Andrew Beaton
title: Homemade Highlights: The Battle for Big Air Snowboarding Gold
text:
American snowboarder Jamie Anderson earned her second medal of the 2018 games after winning gold in slopestyle earlier in the week.
This time, Ms. Anderson won in big air snowboarding, a sport new to the Olympics this year, where snowboarders perform a single trick after barreling down a steep slope and then launching high into the air.
